
1) Install Zohmg:

	$> sudo python install.py


2) Verify that the installation works:

	$> zohmg help


3a) Get help with installing Hadop and HBase in pseudo-distributed mode:

	$> sudo scripts/install_hadoop_hbase.sh

- OR -

3b) If you already have a running Hadoop 0.19 and HBase 0.19 cluster you want to use:

	- Patch the Hadoop installation with HADOOP-1722 and HADOOP-5450
	- Make sure hbase-site.xml is copied to $HADOOP_HOME/conf


4) Please see README for getting started with Zohmg.


